com.mvohm.quadruple.test

Class TestData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mvohm.quadruple.test.TestData

  • public class TestData
extends Object
    Statically defined data sets for testing basic public methods of Quadruple. Provide coverage for all the code of the methods and some corner cases (except most trivial ones that don't require special testing). All the data are static arrays of Strings representing decimal numeric values, generally with precision of 120 decimal digits. Every array contains data for testing a certain operation, like addition or a conversion from one type to another. The arrays consist of logical groups, each group of two (for unary operations and conversions) or three (for binary operations) items represents a test case. The first item of a pair or the two first items of a triplet are the input operands for the corresponding operation, and the last one is a value that should be the result of the operation. In most cases, the expected result may be determined by the code that performs testing, in such cases there may be null or an empty string instead of the expected value, e.g. 
     "3.5", "4.5", "8",   // for addition: 3.5 + 4.5 = 8
 "1", "2", null,      // the testing code will find
                      // that the result should be 3
 ...
 "-1.2345e2345", "",  // for the conversion from Quadruple to double,
                      // the result should be Double.NEGATIVE_INFINITY
    In cases where the operation being tested, when applied to the given operand(s), should throw an exception, the word "Error" is used instead of the expected result, to inform the testing code about the fact that throwing an exception is the correct and expected behavior of the operation.
    There are also two sorts of strings that are interpreted by the testing code in special ways:
    • If the first string of the group starts with "//", such group is considered to contain a comment rather than a test case data, and its first item can be printed by the testing code to the console, depending on the code and/or the execution mode, the subsequent items of the group are ignored in this case.
    • If the first string of the group equals "$_STOP_$" (case-insensitively), it is interpreted as an instruction to quit the test execution.

    Author:
    M.Vokhmentsev

    • Field Detail

      • rough_Q2T_cornerCases

        static String[] rough_Q2T_cornerCases
        A data set to test some corner cases for methods converting Quadruple values to values of other types, except BigDecimal.
        Includes NaN, Infinity, the boundary values of widely used ranges, such as Double.MAX_VALUE, Long.MAX_VALUE, etc., both positive and negative, and some values between them.
        Used to provide coverage for quick-and-dirty checks that are performed at the beginning of most of the conversion methods.

      • rough_Q2BD_cornerCases

        static String[] rough_Q2BD_cornerCases
        A data set to test some corner cases for the method converting Quadruple values to BigDecimal values.
        Includes NaN, Infinity, the boundary values of widely used ranges, such as Double.MAX_VALUE, Long.MAX_VALUE, etc., both positive and negative, and some values between them. Contains expected results ("error" or "0") for the values that have no valid BigDecimal counterparts (NaN, Infinity, -Infinity, -0).
        Used to provide coverage for quick-and-dirty checks that are performed at the beginning of Quadruple.bigDecimalValue() method.

      • rough_l2Q_cornerCases

        static String[] rough_l2Q_cornerCases
        A data set to test some corner cases for Quadruple.assign(long) method.
        Includes Long.MAX_VALUE, Long.MIN_VALUE, and a number of values between them. Used for draft testing of Quadruple.assign(long) method.

      • basic_Q2S_conversionData

        static String[] basic_Q2S_conversionData
        A data set for testing Quadruple.toString() method.
        Each data sample consists of two strings: a string representation of the number to be converted, and the expected result. Covers all execution paths of Quadruple.toString() method.
        Actually, in this data set the expected result can be correctly deduced by the test code in all cases, so all the odd items are nulls.
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.toString() method.
        The number of items must be even.

      • basic_Q2D_conversionData

        static String[] basic_Q2D_conversionData
        A data set for testing the conversion of a Quadruple value to a double value with Quadruple.doubleValue() method.
        Each data sample consists of two strings: a string representation of the number to be converted, and the expected result. The latter is actually needed only in the cases when the value can't be expressed as BigDecimal, which is the return type of TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester.findExpectedResult().
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.doubleValue() method.
        The number of items must be even.

      • basic_Q2L_conversionData

        static String[] basic_Q2L_conversionData
        A data set for testing the conversion of a Quadruple value to a long value with Quadruple.longValue() method.
        Each data sample consists of two strings: a string representation of the number to be converted, and the expected result. Actually, for all data samples from this set the expected results can be correctly deduced by the test code, so all the odd items are nulls.
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.longValue() method.
        The number of items must be even.

      • basic_Q2I_conversionData

        static String[] basic_Q2I_conversionData

        The number of items must be even.

      • basic_Q2BD_conversionData

        static String[] basic_Q2BD_conversionData
        A data set for testing the conversion of a Quadruple value to an BigDecimal value with Quadruple.bigDecimalValue() method.
        Each data sample consists of two strings: a string representation of the number to be converted, and the expected result. For the values that are not valid for BigDecimal, the tested method is expected to throw an exception. The word "Error" is used as a substitute of the expected result in such cases, to inform the test code that throwing an exception is the correct behavior. For all other values, the expected results can be evaluated by the testing code, thus the data contains nulls instead of expected values.
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.bigDecimalValue() method.
        The number of items must be even.

      • special_S2Q_conversionSata

        static String[] special_S2Q_conversionSata
        An auxiliary data set that can be used for testing or debugging Quadruple.bigDecimalValue() with some values of a special interest.
        Each data sample consists of two strings: a string representation of the value to be used for testing or debugging the method, and a string representation of the expected result.
        The number of items must be even.

      • basic_S2Q_conversionData

        static String[] basic_S2Q_conversionData
        A data set for testing Quadruple.assign(String value) method or the constructor that accepts a String parameter.
        Each data sample consists of two strings: a string representation of the value to be assigned, and a string representation of the value that a Quadruple instance is expected to have after the assignment. In most cases the expected value for a sample can be evaluated by the testing code, so nulls are used instead of the expected values.
        Since some special String values can be used as the assignment arguments to designate certain Quadruple values ("min_value", "max_value", etc.), such strings are accompanied with string representations of the corresponding Quadruple values.
        The samples of knowingly unacceptable input strings that are expected to cause an exception during their parsing are accompanied with the word "error", to inform the test code that throwing an exception is the correct behavior for such cases.
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.assign(String value) method.
        The number of items must be even.

      • basic_BD2Q_conversionData

        static String[] basic_BD2Q_conversionData
        A data set for testing Quadruple.assign(BigDecimal value) or the constructor that accepts a BigDecimal parameter.
        Each data sample consists of two strings: a string representation of the value to be assigned, and a string representation of the value that a Quadruple instance is expected to have after the assignment. For any BigDecimal value, the corresponding Quadruple value can be evaluated by the testing code, so nulls are used as the second items for all samples.
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.assign(BigDecimal value) method.
        The number of items must be even.

      • basicAdditionData

        static String[] basicAdditionData
        A data set for testing Quadruple.add(Quadruple) and Quadruple.add(Quadruple, Quadruple) methods.
        Each data sample consists of three strings: two strings representing the values of the operands, and the expected result of their addition.
        For any pair of the operands, the corresponding result can be evaluated by the testing code, thus the data contains nulls instead of the values of the expected results.
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.add(Quadruple) method.
        The number of items must be divisible by 3.

        Is not used in the current version.

      • basicSubtractionData

        static String[] basicSubtractionData
        A data set for testing Quadruple.subtract(Quadruple subtrahend) and Quadruple.add(Quadruple minuend, Quadruple subtrahend) methods.
        Each data sample consists of three strings: string representations of the minuend and the subtrahend, and the expected value of their difference.
        For any pair of the operands, the corresponding result can be evaluated by the testing code, thus the data contains nulls instead of the values of the expected results.

        The number of items must be divisible by 3.

      • basicMultiplicationData

        static String[] basicMultiplicationData
        A data set for testing Quadruple.multiply(Quadruple factor) and Quadruple.multiply(Quadruple factor1, Quadruple factor2) methods.
        Each data sample consists of three strings: string representations of the two factors, and the expected value of their product.
        For most of the pairs of the operands, the corresponding result can be evaluated by the testing code, thus the data in such cases contains nulls instead of the values of the expected results. Exceptions are the cases where the product is subnormal, since subnormal values contain fewer bits in the mantissa than normal values, so the relative error of subnormal values can be much higher than the standard error threshold.
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.multiply(Quadruple factor) method.
        The number of items must be divisible by 3.

        Is not used in the current version.
        The number of items must be divisible by 3.

      • basicSqrtData

        static String[] basicSqrtData
        A data set for testing Quadruple.sqrt() and Quadruple.sqrt(Quadruple) methods.
        Each data sample consists of two strings: a string representation of the argument of sqrt() function to be tested, and the expected result of extracting the square root of this argument. In this data set the expected result can be correctly deduced by the test code in most cases, so most of the odd items are nulls. Exceptions are the cases of negative arguments, for which the expected result is NaN, that is stated explicitely.
        Completely covers the code of the Quadruple.sqrt() method.
